result.execSummary:
The defendant Corey J. Gilbert was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Corey J. Gilbert

records.addlTxt: Reminder Notice indicating amount due mailed to defendant.

(Cases 22CM115, 22CM67, 22CF243, 21CM881 are called at 3:18 PM) Defendant Corey J. Gilbert in court, in custody.  Attorney James H Krave in court for Corey J. Gilbert.  Attorney Tiffany Winter in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Victim/Witness statute complied with. Defense recites the joint sentence recommendation. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Defendant acknowledges receipt of prior convictions. Defendant pleads Guilty to 22CF243 Count 1- Possession of Methamphetamine as Repeater, 22CM115 Count 1- Misdemeanor Battery as Domestic and as Repeater, Count 3- Misdemeanor Bail Jumping as Domestic and as Repeater, 21CM881 Count 1- Misdemeanor Battery as Domestic and as Repeater, Count 4- Misdemeanor Bail Jumping as Domestic and as Repeater. Court accepts pleas and finds the Defendant guilty. Remaining charges are dismissed and read in, including all of 22CM67. Defendant makes a statement. 
Court withholds sentence and orders 24 months Probation with the following conditions: 120 days jail with Huber on 21CM881 Count 1, all stayed pending further order of the court; No contact with B.C., B.H., J.S. without written approval of the agent; Parenting Classes; Domestic Violence assessment; Child exchange through 3rd party; Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations; Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge; Court costs. 80 days credit in 22CM115 if revoked, 2 days credit if revoked in 21CM881 and 22CF243.
Dated 04/21/2022, Letter from Attorney James Krave to Court regarding plea agreement and hearing.

In felony file: Defendant waives their right to a preliminary hearing and Court accepts waiver. Case is referred to Branch 5 to schedule ARGN with misdemeanor files riding along for status.
Plea/sentencing hearing on May 6, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
